pr_review_comment_body:
We have to use PyCObject functions (or the aliases defined in this file). This should be something like:

```
if (mechoidobj != NULL) {
    if (!PyCObject_Check(mechoidobj)) {
        PyErr_SetString(PyExc_TypeError, "Expected a context object for mech_oid");
        goto done;
    } else {
        mechoid = (WCHAR*)PyCObject_AsVoidPtr(mechoidobj);
        if (mechoid == NULL) {
            goto done;
        }
    }
}
```

minor style detail, but closing brackets/parens/etc should line up with the opening.

so in this case I would probably do

```javascript
function _getCurrentChannel() {
  let currentChannelId = null;
  return new Promise((resolve, reject) => {
    //...
  });
}
```

Perhaps consider combining the three bool into a bitfield to save a couple of bytes (every little bit helps, right)?
```
struct {
      bool mEnabled : 1;
      bool mAlwaysAboveThreshold : 1;
      bool mJamState : 1;
} mFlags;
```
Then set / clear with: `this->mFlags.mJamState = true;`
